eak down our global illumination process into multiple passes. We'll do a h=
igh resolution pass with fewer rays, and a lower resolution pass with more =
rays. According to the penumbra hypothesis, that should more accurately mod=
el how lights / shadows behave.</p>
<p>So to start - we need our distance field texture and our scene texture (=
same as before). But this time we'll also need to keep around a <code>lastT=
exture</code> that we'll use to keep around the previous pass.</p>
