<p>In the shader, we're going to make 3 modifications to our original naive=
 gi shader.</p>
<ol>
  <li>Add the ability to render at a lower resolution</li>
  <li>Add the ability to merge with a previous pass</li>
  <li>Add the ability to start and stop at a specified distance from the or=
igin of the raymarch.</li>
</ol>
<p>That last modifications models the behavior in the penumbra hypothesis t=
hat describes how the required resolution drops and required ray count incr=
eases as you move further away. To model that behavior, we need to be able =
to tell our shader to march between a specified interval.</p>
<p>So starting with rendering at a lower resolution - let's just try someth=
ing out.</p>
<p>Let's cut our resolution in half (floor each pixel to half).</p>
